column4: question: I can easily tell if someone else wants to enter a conversation.
column5: question: I really enjoy caring for other people.
column6: question: I find it hard to know what to do in a social situation.
column7: question: I often find it difficult to judge if something is rude or polite.
column8: question: In a conversation, I tend to focus on my own thoughts rather than on what my listener might be thinking.
column9: question: I can pick up quickly if someone says one thing but means another.
column10: question: It is hard for me to see why some things upset people so much.
column11: question: I find it easy to put myself in somebody else’s shoes.
column12: question: I am good at predicting how someone will feel.
column13: question: I am quick to spot when someone in a group is feeling awkward or uncomfortable.
column14: question: I can’t always see why someone should have felt offended by a remark.
column15: question: I don’t tend to find social situations confusing.
column16: question: Other people tell me I am good at understanding how they are feeling and what they are thinking.
column17: question: I can easily tell if someone else is interested or bored with what I am saying.
column18: question: Friends usually talk to me about their problems as they say that I am very understanding.
column19: question: I can sense if I am intruding, even if the other person doesn’t tell me.
column20: question: Other people often say that I am insensitive, though I don’t always see why.a
column21: question: I can tune into how someone else feels rapidly and intuitively.
column22: question: I can easily work out what another person might want to talk about.
column23: question: I can tell if someone is masking their true emotion.
column24: question: I am good at predicting what someone will do.
column25: question: I tend to get emotionally involved with a friend’s problems.
